{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, RC jointly with adaptive feedback control technique can be used to track the unknown and unstable periodic orbits and stabilize them even when the chaotic time series are only available 14.",
    "RC can be applied for scientific computation such as in the numerical solution of PDEs 21, 22, 32.",
    "For these tasks, RC is typically used to evolve the states of the system toward the temporal direction with a flow diagram shown in Fig. 2d.",
    "To decrease the difficulty for a single reservoir to process all inputs and improve the training efficiency, parallel reservoir architecture was proposed 21, 22 which allows multiple small reservoirs to deal with different parts of input data.",
    "The input vector is split into multiple small groups with each group includes some extra adjacent points serving as extra information provided to the corresponding small reservoirs."
  ]
}